  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 9 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 2 critical, 13 high, 7 medium, 17 normal. Key bases needing attention include Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Iaşi (IAS/LRIA) and Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP); plus 12 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and RVR limitations  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV) and Craiova (CRA/LRCV). Network hotspots: Malmö Sturup (MMX/ESMS), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) and 4 others. Primary drivers: very low visibility, low cloud base and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Malmö Sturup (MMX/ESMS), Lennart Meri Tallinn (TLL/EETN), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) and 9 others.",
